Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.83,0:00:02.48,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.86,0:00:03.39,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.94,0:00:04.97,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.81,0:00:07.85,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Like I just said, they've \Ndecided to demolish...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.85,0:00:10.01,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura Hall at the end of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.42,0:00:13.70,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be moving into the regular \Ndorms in April, so start packing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.13,0:00:15.15,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.15,0:00:16.57,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's great news, kouhai-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.09,0:00:19.66,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you been listening to \Nwhat Chihiro-chan's been saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.66,0:00:21.97,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you happy that they're \Ngoing to rebuild Sakura Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.97,0:00:24.25,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm already so excited, I don't \Nknow what to do with myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.25,0:00:26.96,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be able to sleep tonight! \NIn fact, I'd rather sleep through the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.96,0:00:30.59,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,"Rebuild"? Is this actually a positive thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.96,0:00:34.72,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,No. When I said they're getting \Nrid of Sakura Hall, I meant it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.72,0:00:36.23,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,They're not rebuilding it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.23,0:00:37.55,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to disappear completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.12,0:00:41.95,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Chihiro-chan, I don't remember hearing \Nor accepting anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.95,0:00:44.19,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Who made that decision?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.19,0:00:45.79,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,An expert inspected...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.79,0:00:49.06,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the building's condition over winter break.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.57,0:00:50.27,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Winter break?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.64,0:00:51.97,Saku-thought,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.97,0:00:54.60,Saku-thought,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm locking up Sakura Hall \Nat the end of this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.60,0:00:55.11,Saku-thought,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.36,0:00:58.03,Saku-thought,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go have some fun in Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.03,0:00:59.78,Saku-thought,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,You'll all have to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.81,0:01:02.54,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying you tricked us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.84,0:01:05.20,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Sorata.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.95,0:01:08.96,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.46,0:01:11.57,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura Hall {\i1}is{\i0} old, but it's not so old...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.57,0:01:13.71,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,that it needs to be torn down right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.33,0:01:17.85,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,If they have to demolish it, can't they \Nwait until these guys graduate?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.50,0:01:20.42,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you just tell us they \Ndecided to demolish it,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.42,0:01:24.46,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Chihiro-chan, you realize\N we'll fight this decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.15,0:01:26.99,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,It was decided in a board meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.51,0:01:29.06,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,They even gave you permission to keep...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.06,0:01:30.57,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,your cats in the regular \Ndorms for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.88,0:01:31.94,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,That's all. Dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.29,0:01:32.98,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.94,0:01:46.75,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,We can still live in Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.02,0:01:48.74,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll convince the principal \Nto change his mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.74,0:01:49.89,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.89,0:01:52.58,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,If you go after the principal, \Nhe might never recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.05,0:01:54.83,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a good idea to portray Sakura Hall...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.83,0:01:56.30,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,in a worse light than it already is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.76,0:01:58.46,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't accept this!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.46,0:02:01.01,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe they'd ignore the \Nopinions of the current residents.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.01,0:02:04.36,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,She's right. And doing it \Nso underhandedly, too—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.36,0:02:05.39,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.62,0:02:10.31,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki and I are graduating, but for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.31,0:02:13.02,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,this is a unique opportunity \Nto return to the regular dorms.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.37,0:02:14.39,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.39,0:02:16.50,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,The regular dorms are nice and clean,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.50,0:02:18.69,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and you'll never be \Nbothered by drafts again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.69,0:02:21.28,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,The cafeteria workers will \Nprepare your meals for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.76,0:02:25.29,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike this place, you'll never need \Nto worry about various things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.43,0:02:27.39,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the point—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.39,0:02:30.90,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,For you, Kanda, you'll be \Nable to use your free time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.90,0:02:33.51,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,to prepare for the title screening.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.51,0:02:37.59,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Akasaka, don't you care if \NSakura Hall just disappears?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.59,0:02:41.05,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I am calmly weighing the \Npros and cons. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.50,0:02:42.45,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.92,0:02:44.35,Saku-overlap,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's not get ahead of ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.35,0:02:46.81,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,We should consider all of those things, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.00,0:04:21.98,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,To think the first thing \NI heard after coming back...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.98,0:04:23.90,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,was the news of this \Ndorm being demolished.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.29,0:04:27.74,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Jin, does it really not bother you \Nthat Sakura Hall's going to disappear?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.74,0:04:29.34,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.34,0:04:31.09,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,We owe them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.48,0:04:35.33,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's our turn to do \Nwhat we can for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.12,0:04:39.52,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,If we can't convince the \Nprincipal, what should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.52,0:04:42.42,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Their reasoning for suddenly demolishing \Nthis building doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.07,0:04:45.09,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,If it was something they could tell us,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.09,0:04:46.68,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,they would have told us by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.68,0:04:47.59,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.92,0:04:48.79,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, for now...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.62,0:04:55.60,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.04,0:04:59.38,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens, \NI'll take care of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.96,0:05:03.13,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You understand the \Nsituation, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.50,0:05:05.50,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura Hall is going \Nto disappear, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.50,0:05:08.40,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. You know what \Nthat means, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.77,0:05:11.20,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,From April, we'll all live \Nin the regular dorms.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.49,0:05:13.54,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What? I'm surprised you \Nunderstood that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.94,0:05:17.33,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens, \Nyou'll take care of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.33,0:05:18.54,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you didn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.23,0:05:21.79,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, I can't do that \Nin the regular dorms.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.79,0:05:22.38,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.79,0:05:24.94,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Men and women eat separately,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.94,0:05:27.03,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and men can't enter the women's dorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.03,0:05:28.69,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be able to...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.69,0:05:30.85,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,wake you up every morning \Nor cook for you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.85,0:05:31.89,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,That {\i1}is{\i0} a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.34,0:05:40.06,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I like Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.63,0:05:42.80,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.28,0:05:48.57,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I wanted to leave as \Nsoon as I found homes for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.09,0:05:58.58,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That's the picture we took \Nwhen I first arrived here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.22,0:06:00.79,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.79,0:06:04.76,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think of it, \Nthe principal made me move here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.09,0:06:11.76,Sign,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Principal's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.23,0:06:08.36,Saku-main,PRINCIPAL,0000,0000,0000,,Kanda Sorata-kun, do you understand why...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.36,0:06:09.63,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,you've been summoned here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.63,0:06:11.76,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's about my cat, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.27,0:06:14.55,Saku-main,PRINCIPAL,0000,0000,0000,,We've been turning a blind \Neye for the last month,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.55,0:06:17.02,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,but keeping live animals in the \Ndorms is against the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.48,0:06:19.86,Saku-main,PRINCIPAL,0000,0000,0000,,Get rid of the cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.86,0:06:22.60,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,or leave the regular dorms \Nand move into Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.60,0:06:24.48,Saku-main,PRINCIPAL,0000,0000,0000,,Your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.48,0:06:25.43,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I will move into Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.43,0:06:26.11,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Kanda-kun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.68,0:06:27.86,Saku-main,PRINCIPAL,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any regrets?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.23,0:06:29.08,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,None!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.82,0:06:32.15,Saku-main,MIYAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,So, you accepted your fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.15,0:06:34.06,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm at that age...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.06,0:06:35.71,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,when kids like to rebel \Nagainst authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.71,0:06:36.64,Saku-main,MIYAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,You're an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.64,0:06:37.68,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What else could I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.68,0:06:39.62,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me I couldn't keep \Nmy cat in the regular dorms!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.15,0:06:41.96,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really going to \Nmove into Sakura Hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.36,0:06:44.67,Saku-main,MIYAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Once you're exiled to that \Nplace, you're done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.67,0:06:46.61,Saku-main,MIYAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never be able to \Nreturn to a normal life!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.61,0:06:48.74,Saku-main,MIYAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura Hall is the one \Nplace you should never go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.74,0:06:50.56,Saku-main,MIYAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,That's what they say about Sakura Hall!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.56,0:06:51.85,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.85,0:06:53.83,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll find someone to \Ntake Hikari and return...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.83,0:06:56.14,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,to the regular dorms \Nby the second semester.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.14,0:06:57.85,Sign,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.62,0:07:01.56,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,So far, it's about three times \Nmore rundown than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.31,0:07:07.54,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. It's not as though \Naliens or ghosts live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.59,0:07:10.32,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.40,0:07:16.05,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.00,0:07:21.46,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,How careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.20,0:07:25.18,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming in!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.23,0:07:28.71,Saku-thought,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,My room is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.73,0:07:31.86,Sign,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Kanda Sorata
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:31.42,Saku-thought,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Room 101.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.23,0:07:37.32,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty big.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.77,0:07:42.30,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it's been \Nproperly cleaned, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.30,0:07:43.76,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,This place is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.51,0:07:45.94,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,There's even storage...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:51.00,Saku-thought,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'm just too tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.23,0:07:58.79,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Burglar!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.73,0:08:02.50,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You give up, Mr. Burglar?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.77,0:08:03.55,Saku-overlap,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a burglar! I'm a \Nfirst-year student...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.41,0:08:06.87,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, are you the second year, \NKamiigusa-senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.87,0:08:09.04,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,How does a burglar know my name?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.04,0:08:11.16,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.16,0:08:12.91,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You're the art scholarship student...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.91,0:08:15.14,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,who made that hugely popular anime...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.28,0:08:17.15,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Punishment!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.15,0:08:18.50,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You've got the wrong idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.50,0:08:20.06,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kanda Sorata, a first year,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.06,0:08:21.48,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and I'll be living here starting today!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.66,0:08:23.30,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's what all the burglars say!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.30,0:08:24.27,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,No, they don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.23,0:08:27.71,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,This is Hikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.71,0:08:30.47,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,They kicked me out of the regular \Ndorms for owning a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.47,0:08:32.74,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Soratan and Hikarin, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.74,0:08:34.74,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,So you're more of a cat \Nperson than a dog person?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.13,0:08:35.79,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.79,0:08:36.74,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I suppose I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.74,0:08:38.63,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm definitely a "this" person!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.63,0:08:40.12,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Was that even one of the options?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.35,0:08:44.24,Sign,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Soratan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.53,0:08:41.52,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Soratan...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.52,0:08:43.17,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't call me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.17,0:08:44.37,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What am I, a moe character?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.24,0:08:46.24,Sign,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Sorapyon
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.37,0:08:45.32,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then, Sorapyon...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.32,0:08:46.25,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm some lazy mascot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.25,0:08:47.23,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then, Sorani...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.23,0:08:48.00,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm an organic compound...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:50.44,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What don't you like \Nabout them, Soranya?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.44,0:08:52.29,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Friends give each other nicknames.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.29,0:08:53.83,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,My head's starting to hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.83,0:08:54.94,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Tan-Tan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.94,0:08:56.76,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't even resemble \Nmy name anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.23,0:08:58.93,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,The CEO of a certain company...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.93,0:09:01.97,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,would go jogging in the \Npark every morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.97,0:09:02.63,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.63,0:09:05.39,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,The park was littered with empty cans.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.39,0:09:08.45,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Unable to ignore them, the CEO decided...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.45,0:09:11.11,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,to pick one up every \Nday he went jogging.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.95,0:09:14.18,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,But because a lot more cans...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.18,0:09:16.95,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,were thrown away than \Nthe CEO could pick up,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.95,0:09:19.24,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,there were increasingly \Nmore cans, not fewer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.62,0:09:23.07,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,But the CEO kept picking \Ncans up every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.72,0:09:26.77,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievably, after a \Nconsiderable length of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.77,0:09:29.46,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,the number of cans began decreasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:35.59,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Truth was, other runners \Nwere inspired by the CEO...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.59,0:09:39.26,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and had begun picking up cans, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.20,0:09:43.70,Sign,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Fin
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.64,0:09:42.97,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like a nice story...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.97,0:09:44.24,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It is a nice story!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.24,0:09:46.44,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It means humans aren't so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.44,0:09:48.20,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Even though some throw away cans.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.20,0:09:50.60,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,So, why did you suddenly \Ntell me this nice story?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.60,0:09:51.48,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,No reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.06,0:09:53.55,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,An alien!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.55,0:09:54.02,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Where?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.02,0:09:54.99,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.99,0:09:57.09,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're a funny kid, Sorachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.09,0:09:59.03,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I was called funny by someone\N who's funny in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.03,0:10:00.49,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.85,0:10:02.23,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,What's all the fuss about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.91,0:10:04.31,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.31,0:10:05.12,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.12,0:10:06.44,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm moving in today...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.44,0:10:09.46,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. The principal \Nsaid something crazy...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.46,0:10:12.84,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,about a student joining Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.08,0:10:15.07,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It's not crazy at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.07,0:10:16.84,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Sensei, why are \Nyou dressed like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.20,0:10:19.34,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on my way to a mixer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.34,0:10:22.01,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have time to \Nworry about my students.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.01,0:10:23.29,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.54,0:10:25.11,Saku-overlap,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a boy or girl? Boy or girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.29,0:10:25.87,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Why does summer have to be so hot?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.11,0:10:27.11,Saku-overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,A girl! So you're Hikari-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.87,0:10:27.09,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't make any sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.41,0:10:30.82,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like my heart is breaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.60,0:10:33.25,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,What have you been shouting about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.25,0:10:36.28,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Jin, it's Soran! He's moving \Ninto Room 101 today!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.68,0:10:38.70,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Then, his surname must be Yaren.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.70,0:10:41.47,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It's not! I'm Kanda Sorata, a freshman!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.47,0:10:43.16,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,And this is Hikarin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.16,0:10:46.46,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, so you're the kid with the \Ncat from the regular dorms.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.92,0:10:49.50,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Mitaka Jin. I'm in Room 103.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.50,0:10:50.25,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.25,0:10:52.25,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, Mitaka-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.85,0:10:54.88,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call me Senpai. Just call me Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.30,0:10:58.05,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, Jin-san, I'd appreciate \Nit if you could help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.77,0:11:00.11,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki, go easy on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.11,0:11:01.46,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That's all you're going to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.46,0:11:03.42,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's you asking, \NJin, I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.42,0:11:05.66,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I want to become even \Nbetter friends with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.88,0:11:06.28,Saku-thought,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't use honorifics?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.28,0:11:08.49,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki and I are childhood friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.49,0:11:11.40,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, that's not the full \Nextent of our relationship...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.06,0:11:14.00,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,My girlfriend is a married woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.00,0:11:15.28,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to go on a date with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.28,0:11:15.73,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.10,0:11:16.77,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.77,0:11:18.69,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?! What did Jin say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.16,0:11:21.75,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, keep it together, Soranyan!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.75,0:11:23.73,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.99,0:11:26.16,Sign,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.26,0:11:32.88,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.88,0:11:34.36,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's 98 wins in a row!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.36,0:11:36.21,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Only two more for 100 consecutive wins!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.02,0:11:39.85,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to unpack my stuff soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.85,0:11:41.42,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You can do that anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.42,0:11:43.68,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're living here from \Nnow on, Sora-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.98,0:11:47.67,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving as soon as I find \Nsomeone to take Hikari!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.67,0:11:49.39,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Save it for after you've beaten me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.69,0:11:56.14,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's 99 wins in a row!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.14,0:11:58.82,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,After all the time I've \Nspent playing this game...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.82,0:12:01.31,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I believe professional wrestlers \Nare the greatest warriors!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.31,0:12:03.29,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Professional wrestlers \Nare really strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.29,0:12:05.03,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You're just needlessly strong, Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.76,0:12:07.91,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Could I at least take a bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.43,0:12:10.35,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you? A little girl \Nworried she might stink...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.35,0:12:11.91,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,of sweat in front of the boy she likes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.32,0:12:13.54,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,"Why are you standing so far away?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.54,0:12:16.13,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,"N-No reason. Stay away."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.64,0:12:18.38,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,"What's your problem? \NDo what you want."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.38,0:12:19.67,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You'll give him the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.11,0:12:21.93,Saku-thought,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm a guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.93,0:12:23.72,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm going to go take a bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.72,0:12:25.84,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You're abandoning \Nyour 100 win streak?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.84,0:12:27.81,Sign,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Girl In Bathroom!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.17,0:12:31.91,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll have some \Nwater and try to relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.91,0:12:32.60,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.04,0:12:37.70,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What could be making that \Nnoise at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.41,0:12:44.14,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sensei? Or is it you, Jin-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.14,0:12:45.50,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Are you back already?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.63,0:12:56.66,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,G-G-G...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.68,0:13:00.83,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,G-G-G-Gho...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.87,0:13:06.39,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,The room next door...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.07,0:13:09.41,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That was a real live person, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.04,0:13:12.31,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you screaming about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.64,0:13:14.81,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Another monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:17.37,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,You got a death wish or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.37,0:13:18.98,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Sensei. It's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.98,0:13:20.48,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You're back from your mixer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.48,0:13:21.28,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,A long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.68,0:13:24.76,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,All of them sucked, but they \Nkept going on about how...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.76,0:13:27.07,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,my personality's terrible \Nand I drink too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.40,0:13:28.36,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Those idiots!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.36,0:13:31.54,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, I just saw a g-g-gho—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.54,0:13:33.69,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,You saying I look old and withered? \NI'm still in my twenties.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.69,0:13:35.08,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody said anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.08,0:13:36.24,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I just saw a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.24,0:13:38.09,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Its hair reached all the \Nway down to its waist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.09,0:13:40.38,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It disappeared into the \Nroom next to mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.68,0:13:42.76,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. He comes out\N of there sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.76,0:13:44.55,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,So there is a ghost?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.55,0:13:47.02,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Akasaka Ryunosuke in Room 102.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.02,0:13:47.47,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.47,0:13:53.20,Sign,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Kanda Sorata      Akasaka Ryunosuke      Mitaka Jin
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.11,0:13:50.39,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I'd completely forgotten about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.39,0:13:53.41,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I've only seen him about three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.20,0:13:57.96,Sign,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Akasaka Ryunosuke
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.41,0:13:55.93,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, don't you look \Nafter this place?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.93,0:13:58.39,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Akasaka's an extreme recluse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.39,0:14:00.12,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,He's a first year like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.12,0:14:02.73,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,but he hasn't gone to school \Nonce since he enrolled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.73,0:14:06.97,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,You're pretty lucky to meet Akasaka \Non the day you moved in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.97,0:14:09.39,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't treat a reclusive student...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.39,0:14:10.62,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,like some kind of good luck fairy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:12.28,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,It really is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.28,0:14:14.81,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Your reaction is far more amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.81,0:14:17.90,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, isn't it your responsibility \Nto make him go to school?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.90,0:14:19.84,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Making someone do something \Nthey don't want to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.84,0:14:21.63,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,will just make their life unpleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.24,0:14:24.40,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You've thought this through.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.79,0:14:25.74,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.74,0:14:28.63,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I don't do any \Nwork at Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.63,0:14:29.32,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.32,0:14:30.78,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You were talking about yourself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.78,0:14:31.22,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.47,0:14:32.28,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.28,0:14:34.59,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to talk to Akasaka, text him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.59,0:14:35.48,Saku-main,CHIHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,That's his number.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.48,0:14:35.81,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.57,0:14:43.23,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,He lives in the room next to \Nmine and I have to text him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.68,0:14:47.63,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see. That should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.94,0:14:47.58,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Composing Message{\b0}\NMy name's Kanda Sorata, and I've moved \Ninto Room 101. Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.58,0:14:49.58,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Sending
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.82,0:14:50.53,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Message Received {\b0}\NAkasaka Ryunosuke
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.91,0:14:52.80,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That was quick. What's it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.15,0:14:57.96,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,"Ryunosuke-sama is currently developing \Na motion engine... okay?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.96,0:15:02.46,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Akasaka Ryunosuke{\b0}\N {\b1}Subject: none{\b0}\N Ryunosuke-sama is currently developing a motion engine,\N okay? He cannot answer your message, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.84,0:15:01.68,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,"He cannot answer your message, okay?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.18,0:15:04.18,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,"Yours sincerely, the recently \Nborn Maid-chan."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.87,0:15:09.19,Saku-thought,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Um, how am I supposed \Nto interpret this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.02,0:15:13.08,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Akasaka, you're a funny guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.97,0:15:15.47,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Akasaka Ryunosuke\NSubject: What's the joke?{\b0}\NMaid-chan is working as hard as \Nshe can, okay? From Maid-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.57,0:15:19.44,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,"Maid-chan is working as \Nhard as she can, okay?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.98,0:15:21.11,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,"From Maid-chan."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.28,0:15:24.88,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:26.69,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you talk to me normally?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.96,0:15:31.44,Sign,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,I am talking normally, okay? Sorata-kun, you\N must be a stupid kid, okay? From Maid-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.63,0:15:35.11,Sign,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Akasaka-kun, could you stop ending your\N sentences like that? It's annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.02,0:15:33.80,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What's up with this conversation?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.26,0:15:36.85,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,I am not Ryunosuke-sama, okay? From Maid-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.06,0:15:39.35,Sign,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous! Quit making fun of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.09,0:15:38.63,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.63,0:15:40.29,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Quit making fun of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.94,0:15:42.57,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Message Received{\b0} \NAkasaka Ryunosuke
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.74,0:15:46.37,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,"Maid-chan is an AI program \NI created to answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.37,0:15:48.48,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,my messages automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.48,0:15:50.74,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,She composes appropriate responses...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.74,0:15:53.05,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,within a second of receiving \Na message and sends replies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.05,0:15:55.26,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't even figure that out?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.26,0:15:57.47,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Akasaka Ryunosuke{\b0} \N{\b1}Subject: none{\b0}\N Don't waste my time. Akasaka Ryunosuke
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.78,0:15:59.37,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,No one would expect you to use...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.37,0:16:02.22,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,an automatic answering program \Nfor your personal number!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.06,0:16:05.31,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Akasaka Ryunosuke \NSubject: I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.31,0:16:11.20,Sign,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea someone existed in this world \Nwho couldn't understand that. Sorry. That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.32,0:16:08.25,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,"I had no idea someone existed...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.25,0:16:11.20,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,in this world who couldn't understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.53,0:16:13.28,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. That's all."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.48,0:16:16.37,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel like I've been \Napologized to at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.37,0:16:17.92,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.92,0:16:19.28,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't waiting for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.28,0:16:20.86,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorachi, let's play Metal Cluster next.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.86,0:16:23.24,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Isn't that a single-player game?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.24,0:16:24.82,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll play in turns and compare our scores.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.82,0:16:26.25,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Watch me play for about three hours first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.25,0:16:27.94,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be morning by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.94,0:16:31.60,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, why did you come \Ndressed like that? Please leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.23,0:16:31.60,Saku-overlap,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't sweat the small stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.60,0:16:32.72,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Sit down, Sorapu.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.37,0:16:36.64,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. If you won't leave, \NKamiigusa-senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.96,0:16:38.61,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Then I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.61,0:16:41.64,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stay here any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.18,0:16:41.64,Saku-overlap,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Sorapi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.59,0:16:48.23,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What am I going to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.33,0:16:58.98,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,No! Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.98,0:17:02.26,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way they'd let \Nme keep a second one!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.35,0:17:14.75,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.32,0:17:18.43,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Keep quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.43,0:17:19.76,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.78,0:17:23.57,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Jin-san, did you just get home?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.57,0:17:25.77,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Meiko-san didn't give \Nme a chance to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.08,0:17:27.48,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,H-How adult of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:29.36,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Is Meiko-san someone else's wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.66,0:17:32.03,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I have three other \Ngirlfriends, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.03,0:17:33.27,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You have four girlfriends?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.27,0:17:35.40,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,And who's your cutie there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.83,0:17:38.55,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I picked her up in the park...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.55,0:17:40.17,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Ah. What's her name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.17,0:17:41.66,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking of calling her Nozomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.07,0:17:44.08,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,If you pick up a third one, \Nyou'll have to call her Kodama.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.08,0:17:46.12,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,There won't be a third.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.12,0:17:49.46,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not even sure they'll \Nlet me keep a second one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.86,0:17:56.60,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to Sakura Hall!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.26,0:18:09.09,Sign,BANNER,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to Sakura Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.59,0:17:58.06,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.06,0:18:00.01,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, it's a new \Nresident welcoming party.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.01,0:18:01.99,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It's six in the morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.99,0:18:04.10,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki insisted on doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.39,0:18:06.27,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I wandered home at this hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.72,0:18:10.56,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you went out so I could \Nmake it a surprise, Sorakyun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.08,0:18:13.26,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,You did this all yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.63,0:18:17.03,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Misaki was looking forward \Nto having a new resident.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.60,0:18:20.91,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,She's been keeping this \Nroom clean by herself...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.91,0:18:22.97,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,so it'd always be ready \Nfor someone to move in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.98,0:18:27.12,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it was so tidy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.68,0:18:29.10,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,But why hotpot?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.47,0:18:32.51,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,We always serve hotpot at \NSakura Hall welcoming parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.51,0:18:33.91,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but in the middle of summer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.91,0:18:35.72,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about that. Sit, sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.79,0:18:42.46,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.71,0:18:45.58,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that? Is she a new resident, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.91,0:18:48.80,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I just picked her up in the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.80,0:18:50.81,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I was hoping it'd be all right \Nfor me to keep another cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.11,0:18:53.15,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hold a Sakura Hall meeting, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.15,0:18:54.55,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,A Sakura Hall meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.55,0:18:56.34,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,When we have to make a decision,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.34,0:18:58.46,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,we hold a meeting with all the residents.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.91,0:19:00.37,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Her name's Nozomi, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.88,0:19:04.13,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, who thinks it would \Nbe fine to keep Nozomi? Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.94,0:19:07.04,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Ryunosuke has no objections, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.04,0:19:07.58,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.21,0:19:11.03,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you want to make \Nthis decision so easily?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.03,0:19:12.33,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What about the teacher's permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.33,0:19:13.15,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.15,0:19:16.34,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,That's how this place works.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.74,0:19:20.68,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Let's keep partying!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.68,0:19:23.55,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Nozomi! Hikari! Kouhai-kun! Eat up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.09,0:19:25.18,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's use that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.18,0:19:25.63,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.63,0:19:26.54,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,My nickname.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.54,0:19:29.39,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to call me \Nkouhai-kun, Kamiigusa-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.73,0:19:32.30,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You can call me by my name, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.30,0:19:34.61,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,We're friends now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.20,0:19:38.02,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Misaki-senpai it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.87,0:19:41.20,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Get a little closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.20,0:19:45.20,Sign,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.46,0:19:42.97,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What about Akasaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.97,0:19:45.20,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about him. \NI'll add him in later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.54,0:19:46.44,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Add him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.44,0:19:49.80,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting to get the feeling \Nwe'll be together for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.80,0:19:51.64,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't joke about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.64,0:19:53.50,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to find owners for these cats...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.50,0:19:54.70,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and leave by the second semester!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.70,0:19:57.09,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, kouhai-kun! \NWe're taking the picture!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.09,0:19:58.01,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Strike a pose!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.39,0:20:00.98,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm definitely leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.20,0:20:15.30,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,It was only Hikari at first...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.77,0:20:20.36,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Komachi made these scratches.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.06,0:20:26.62,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I've tripped down these stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.20,0:20:30.30,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,And I've fixed the front \Ndoor plenty of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.21,0:20:37.63,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura Hall is definitely rundown.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.63,0:20:39.65,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's cold in the winter \Nand hot in the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.34,0:20:42.50,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,The floor in the hallway falls \Nthrough from time to time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.93,0:20:46.66,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and the lock on my door is broken,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.66,0:20:48.82,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,so I have no privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.80,0:20:51.88,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,The second floor leaks, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.49,0:20:52.98,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.38,0:20:58.07,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I realize now that everything that \Nused to bother me has turned into memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.65,0:21:01.69,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,When the bath broke and we went \Nto the public baths together.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.49,0:21:04.61,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,When we took out that hornet nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.63,0:21:07.82,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.17,0:21:12.29,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I've been filling up my journal \Nfaster since I came to Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.03,0:21:15.99,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I'd be losing \Nsomething important...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.48,0:21:18.59,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,if Sakura Hall disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.28,0:21:20.36,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.70,0:21:24.28,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Well said, kouhai-kun. \NYou're exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.28,0:21:26.54,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,The hotpot party on the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.54,0:21:28.79,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Turning Sakura Hall into a \Nhaunted house over the summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.79,0:21:30.67,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and inviting all the kids \Nin the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.67,0:21:34.19,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Playing possum every day \Nwhen you came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.19,0:21:35.85,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,They're all wonderful memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.85,0:21:40.32,Saku-main,JIN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, all your memories also involve \Nsomeone getting mad at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.02,0:21:45.43,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,A lot has happened, but I \Nbelieve we belong here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.04,0:21:48.09,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Akasaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.40,0:21:51.89,Saku-main,AKASAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Pros and cons aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.26,0:21:54.96,Sign,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1}Sender: Mitaka Jin \NSubject: The real reason for tearing down the building {\b0}\NCan you hack the server and investigate?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.89,0:21:54.96,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,it disgusts me that their reason \Nfor doing this isn't clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.32,0:22:01.42,Saku-main,MASHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I like Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.94,0:22:03.59,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,So do I. That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.37,0:22:05.84,Saku-main,SORATA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll stop them from tearing it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.47,0:22:07.11,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.11,0:22:07.84,Saku-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.84,0:22:10.47,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's hold a Sakura Hall meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.86,0:22:13.58,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,The curtain's rising on our \Nfirst defense of Sakura Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.24,0:22:17.79,Eptitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,1290)}#19 There's No Place Like Sakura Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.58,0:22:15.10,Saku-main,MISAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Is everyone ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.10,0:22:16.36,Saku-main,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.65,0:23:33.64,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I don't have any \Ntime to get all depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.64,0:23:34.84,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Life has its ups and downs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.82,0:23:40.97,NextEptitle,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(458,1)}#20 So We Can Keep Saying We're Home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.84,0:23:36.81,Saku-main,NANAMI,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I'd fall any farther.
